  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pilot Assessment of the Needs of Families Searching for Relatives Lost in the Central and Western Mediterranean</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on the data-driven work of IOM&#x2019;s Missing Migrants Project over the past five years, Global Migration Data Analysis Centre (GMDAC) is carrying out a 18-month research project that seeks to shed light on the needs of families of those who have disappeared during migration along the Central and Western Mediterranean routes to Europe. Qualitative research, guided by an advisory board of experts, will be conducted with families and communities of the missing in five research sites, that include places of origin, transit and destination. The research findings will be published as policy briefings that will include recommendations for how different actors can better support families of missing migrants.</narrative>
  </description>
